        <text>
                <body>
                        <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Erasmus of Rotterdam (Brussels, 25
                                        June 1534)</head>
                                <floatingText type="regesta">
                                        <body>
                                                <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He is briefly responding to
                                                  his letter of 22 April, lest he misses the
                                                  courier. Thomas More is said to still be in
                                                  captivity, and John Fisher is not safe, either.
                                                  Erasmus’ health worries him, he would be happy if
                                                  he returned. According to Erasmus, the marquess
                                                  will not do anything against Michaël Hillen von
                                                  Hoochstraaten; but Erasmus is afraid of the monks,
                                                  too. Oláh does not understand what he should be
                                                  afraid of, only the Lutherans are to be feared. 2.
                                                  There is no need to thank for his services for
                                                  Erasmus. Oláh will go where fate calls him, but he
                                                  really wishes he were home, his brothers, friends,
                                                  and others are looking forward to welcoming him
                                                  back home, but the situation is quite turbulent
                                                  there now.</p>
                                        </body>
                                </floatingText>
                                <pb/>
                                <p xml:id="p.1">Nicolai Olai ad Desyderium Erasmum Roterodamum. </p>
                                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] <app xml:id="app.1">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.1">Salutem
                                                  plurimam!</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.1"/>
                                        </app> Litteras, quas ad me XXII. Aprilis dedisti,<note
                                                type="critic" xml:id="note.1">Ep.
                                                  482.<ref>olahus.tei.15340422_1</ref></note> XII.
                                        Maii praeteriti accepi. Nuntium hunc nolui sine meis
                                        litteris ad te proficisci. Ad litteras igitur tuas breviter
                                        accipe. </p>
                                <p xml:id="p.3">Angliae <persName>regis</persName><note
                                                type="critic" xml:id="note.2">King Henry
                                                VIII.</note><app xml:id="app.2">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.2">res</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.2">actiones</rdg>
                                        </app> scribis te ex parte credere. At credes brevi in
                                        omnibus. <persName>Morus</persName><note type="critic"
                                                xml:id="note.3">Thomas More.</note> adhuc captus
                                        esse dicitur cum <app xml:id="app.3">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.3">Rofensi</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.3">Roffensi</rdg>
                                        </app>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.4">John
                                                Fisher.</note> non sine periculo, ut aiunt. Valetudo
                                        tua est mihi <app xml:id="app.4">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.4">molestissima</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.4">ingratissima</rdg>
                                        </app>, cuperem, ut bene valeres et redires.
                                                <persName>Marchionem</persName><note type="critic"
                                                xml:id="note.5">William van den Werwe.</note> nihil
                                        facturum scribis <persName>Hillenio</persName>.<note
                                                type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Michaël Hillen von
                                                Hoochstraaten</note> Times <app xml:id="app.5">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.5">monachos</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.5">funigeros</rdg>
                                        </app>. Si factus es tam timidus, et in <app xml:id="app.6">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.6">eo</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.6">hoc timore</rdg>
                                        </app> constans esse <app xml:id="app.7">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.7">pergis</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.7">perges</rdg>
                                        </app>, non facile tibi <app xml:id="app.8">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.8">hunc</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.8"><del corresp="Olahus"
                                                  >hinc</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                                                  >eum</add></rdg>
                                        </app> exhaurire possum <app xml:id="app.9">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.9">timorem</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.9"/>
                                        </app>, nihil tamen video, quod <app xml:id="app.10">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.10">tibi hic</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.10">hic tibi</rdg>
                                        </app> magnopere esset timendum. Si <app xml:id="app.11">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.11">vereris</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.11">times</rdg>
                                        </app> obtrectationes hominum nostrae aetatis, ab <app
                                                xml:id="app.12">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.12">his</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.12">eis</rdg>
                                        </app> nec tu, nec alii, dum vivunt, liberi esse possunt.
                                        Hic parum, istic ubi <app xml:id="app.13">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.13">nunc</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.13"/>
                                        </app> es <app xml:id="app.14">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.14">existimo
                                                  plurimum</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.14">plurimum
                                                  existimo</rdg>
                                        </app> tibi <app xml:id="app.15">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.15">posse (quod
                                                  absit)</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.15"/>
                                        </app> imminere mali, si praesentium temporum conditionem
                                                <app xml:id="app.16">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.16"
                                                  >consideraveris</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.16">consideraris</rdg>
                                        </app>. Cave igitur milites <app xml:id="app.17">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.17">Luteranos</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.17">Lutheranos</rdg>
                                        </app>, quorum fortasse rabies ad ea usque loca, ubi <app
                                                xml:id="app.18">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.18">nunc agis, (di
                                                  malum hoc prohibeant) brevi</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.18">es, di id
                                                  prohibeant</rdg>
                                        </app> penetrabunt. </p>
                                <p xml:id="p.4">[2.] Meum in te officium, de quo scribis, tale est,
                                        ut nihil <app xml:id="app.19">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.19">a te aliud</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.19">aliud a te</rdg>
                                        </app> exigat, quam testimonium tui erga me amoris et <app
                                                xml:id="app.20">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.20">utque</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.20">ut</rdg>
                                        </app> Olaum tuum ames. Reditum meum in Hungariam scribis
                                        tibi incommodum futurum, sive huc redeas, sive non.
                                        Quocumque me fata vocent, tuum, quem nosti, <app
                                                xml:id="app.21">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.21">omnibus in
                                                  locis</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.21"/>
                                        </app> habebis Olaum. Utinam, mi Erasme, salvis rebus
                                        reverti possem, nihil eo esset mihi iucundius. Patria, <app
                                                xml:id="app.22">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.22">fratres, amici et
                                                  alii </lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.22">amici, fratres</rdg>
                                        </app><app xml:id="app.23">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.23"/>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.23">et</rdg>
                                        </app> necessitudine <app xml:id="app.24">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.24">intima</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.24"/>
                                        </app> mihi iuncti me hortantur, ut redeam. Sed id quam
                                        commode nunc facere possim, rebus non modo Hungaricis
                                                <milestone unit="pb"/>et publicis et meis quoque
                                        privatis, sed etiam aliis regiis, non <app xml:id="app.25">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.25">sine magno
                                                  malo</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.25">minimum</rdg>
                                        </app> turbatis, vix <app xml:id="app.26">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.26">statuere
                                                  statis</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.26">statis statuere</rdg>
                                        </app> possum, huius rei causa tempori serviendum esse
                                        arbitror. Apud <persName>reginam</persName> meam, ducem
                                                <persName>Arscoti</persName>,<note type="critic"
                                                xml:id="note.7">Philippe II de
                                                Croÿ.</note><persName>Panormitanum</persName><note
                                                type="critic" xml:id="note.8">Jean II
                                                Carondelet.</note> fui, tibi vice epistolae et quae
                                        voluisti, eis retuli. Vale et me, ut soles, ama. </p>
                                <p xml:id="p.5"><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 25. Iunii 1534.</p>
                                <p xml:id="p.6">
                                        <app xml:id="app.27">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.27">Tuus, ut nosti.
                                                  Olaus etc.</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.27"/>
                                        </app>
                                </p>
                                <p xml:id="p.7">
                                        <app xml:id="app.28">
                                                <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.28">Excellentissimo
                                                  viro domino Erasmo Roterodamo, sacrae theologiae
                                                  doctori etc., domino et amico praecipuo et
                                                  observandissimo.</lem>
                                                <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.28"/>
                                        </app>
                                </p>
                        </div>
                </body>
